sql:
SELECT AVG(gs.rushing_yards) AS average_rushing_yards
FROM game_statistics gs
WHERE gs.player_id NOT IN (
  SELECT s.player_id
  FROM suspensions s
);

SELECT AVG(tackles) AS average_tackles
FROM injuries AS T1
INNER JOIN game_statistics AS T2 ON T1.player_id = T2.player_id;

external_knowledge:
- A conference typically refers to a group of sports teams that compete against each other;
- The query assumes that each game involves exactly one home team and one away team;
- The team with the highest number of games played will appear first in the results.

- "top 5 teams" refers to the teams with the highest total number of games played;
- "played the most games" includes both home and away games;
- "stars that have shone the brightest" is a metaphorical expression to highlight the teams with the highest activity in the league.

- A "home team" is the team hosting the game;
- An "away team" is the team visiting the home team's venue;
- "Different conferences" means the home and away teams belong to different conferences.

- 'Injured or Suspended' refers to players who have had at least one injury or suspension;
- 'Better Passer' refers to players who have more total passing yards than rushing yards;
- 'Better Runner' refers to players who have more total rushing yards than passing yards.

- "2023" refers to the year of the game;
- "2022" refers to the year of the suspension;
- "Hosted games" implies the team was the home team in the game.

sql:
SELECT DISTINCT T1.player_id
FROM awards T1
INNER JOIN suspensions T2 ON T1.player_id = T2.player_id;

SELECT DISTINCT T.team_name
FROM teams T
INNER JOIN (
  SELECT player_id FROM (
    SELECT player_id FROM injuries WHERE injury_date > '2022-10-15'
  ) AS injuries_subquery
  INTERSECT
  SELECT player_id FROM (
    SELECT player_id FROM suspensions WHERE reason = 'Substance abuse'
  ) AS suspensions_subquery
  INTERSECT
  SELECT player_id FROM (
    SELECT player_id FROM game_statistics WHERE passing_yards > 100
  ) AS game_stats_subquery
) AS players_subquery ON T.team_id = players_subquery.player_id;

external_knowledge:
- 'Mountain West' conference is a collegiate athletic conference;
- 'PNG' is a file format used for images, particularly logos;
- Total yards include passing yards, rushing yards, and receiving yards.
